Package: DAESC
Type: Package
Title: Differential Allelic Expression using Single-Cell data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Guanghao Qi
Maintainer: Guanghao Qi <gqi1@jhu.edu>
Description: DAESC is a software for differential allele-specific expression (ASE) analysis using single-cell RNA-seq data of multiple individuals. It can be applied to any comparison of interested that can be represented by a design matrix, including but not limited to: 1) discrete cell types 2) continuous cell states (e.g. pseudotime) 3) case-control disease status 4) continuous phenotype of the donors (e.g. BMI, blood pressure). DAESC includes two components: DAESC-BB and DAESC-Mix.
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
